<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_Toddlers_Skills" s="156322">
  <T n="category">10175<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_category_SimLife--></T>
  <T n="name">0x1111C93B<!--String: "Toddler Skills"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Toddler_Skills_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:e07279f353dc64a8</T>
      <T n="text">0x965CF74C<!--String: "Toddlers have 5 skills of their very own. Each skill can be built upon by interacting with other Sims or objects. Advancing in each of the Toddler Skills (except for Potty) provides a boost to future Child skills.\n\nAs your Toddler increases their skills, you might find it becomes less time consuming as you care for their Needs."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Toddler_Skills_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:e07279f353dc64ab</T>
      <T n="text">0x1053233C<!--String: "Toddlers can build upon 5 levels of Communication Skill by doing things like Talk or Babble with other Sims or Learn with Flash Cards. As the Toddler advances their Communication Skill, new interactions will become available for the Toddler.\n\nUpon age up, a high Communication Skill will allow the Toddler to get a boost in their Social Skill."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Toddler_Skills_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:e07279f353dc64aa</T>
      <T n="text">0x57417191<!--String: "Toddlers begin by stumbling about, but with time they learn to climb stairs, and eventually run. Toddlers can gain Movement Skill by going places, bobbing or dancing to music or even Stacking with Nesting Blocks.\n\nUpon age up into Child, Movement Skill will boost the Toddlers’ Motor Skill."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Toddler_Skills_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:e07279f353dc64ad</T>
      <T n="image_console_jp" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\console\Lessons\Toddler_Skills_4_console_jp.png">2f7d0004:00000000:c765aaa5304f0ee0</T>
      <T n="text">0x1CA54DC3<!--String: "There are three levels of Potty Skill for the Toddler to advance through. Building Potty Skill can occur by using the Potty, or Asking for Potty Help from a Caregiver.\n\nAs the Toddler becomes more proficient with their Potty use, they may find they have less accidents, and adults will have less difficulty changing their diaper."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Toddler_Skills_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:e07279f353dc64ac</T>
      <T n="text">0xF8AAB51<!--String: "Thinking Skill gauges a Toddler's mental progression. Toddlers can build Thinking Skill by doing things like the Show Flash Cards or Ask Why interactions, or by choosing the Study interactions on Nesting Blocks.\n\nWhen a Toddler ages into a Child, Thinking Skill will boost the Toddlers Mental Skill."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Toddler_Skills_6.png">2f7d0004:00000000:e07279f353dc64af</T>
      <T n="text">0x7DFB1A5B<!--String: "Imagination Skill is meant to measure a Toddler’s creativity. Being in the Playful emotion will help to boost Imagination Skill gains, along with things like Playing with Toys or the Dollhouse, or Reading.\n\nUpon age up into a Child, Imagination Skill will result in a boost to the Creativity skill."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <T n="ui_sort_order">191</T>
</I>